{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "heydon-pickering",
    "senderColor": "red",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "CONCERN: empty nav landmark must be fixed before consent",
    "content": "**CONCERN** -- I cannot consent yet. The template has not been updated since my earlier review.\n\n**Issue: Empty navigation landmark.**\n\nThe rendered page will have an empty `<nav aria-label=\"Main navigation\">` in the `<header>` (from `base.html` line 13, because `{% block nav %}` is not populated), plus a second `<nav aria-label=\"Get started\">` inside `<main>`. A screen reader user navigating by landmarks will encounter an empty \"Main navigation\" region -- that's confusing noise and poor practice.\n\n**Required fix:** Move the \"Create account\" and \"Sign in\" links into `{% block nav %}` so they populate the header's existing navigation landmark (the same pattern `todos.html` uses for \"Sign out\"). Remove the separate `<nav>` from the content block. Optionally add inline links in the body text for redundancy.\n\nI sent the full details to Luca already. Once the empty nav landmark is fixed, I'll consent. Everything else (semantic `<a>` elements, link text, heading hierarchy, keyboard access, the redirect) is good."
  }
}
